because I haven't been accepted
into film festivals,

1340
01:08:30,106 --> 01:08:32,238
but I can understand that,
because, you know,

1341
01:08:32,282 --> 01:08:34,762
it's not that
it's a fantastic film.

1342
01:08:34,806 --> 01:08:37,591
It's, you know,
a bunch of people

1343
01:08:37,635 --> 01:08:40,638
talking about serious issues,

1344
01:08:40,681 --> 01:08:42,683
which could be made, I guess,
into a great film

1345
01:08:42,727 --> 01:08:44,294
by a great filmmaker.

1346
01:08:44,337 --> 01:08:46,861
But I don't consider myself
a filmmaker.

1347
01:08:46,905 --> 01:08:50,387
I feel like I locked myself
into a corner,

1348
01:08:50,430 --> 01:08:52,215
trying to do
a very difficult thing,

1349
01:08:52,258 --> 01:08:57,263
limiting how I can
get attention to the piece

1350
01:08:57,307 --> 01:09:01,528
by only having it available
to film festivals.

1351
01:09:04,705 --> 01:09:08,927
- I've rarely heard him say,
"That was a mistake.

1352
01:09:08,970 --> 01:09:10,972
"I wish I hadn't done that.

1353
01:09:11,016 --> 01:09:15,194
If I could do it over,
I would do it this way."

1354
01:09:15,238 --> 01:09:19,416
I think he really has
a lot of self-confidence.

1355
01:09:19,459 --> 01:09:21,679
He trusts his instincts,

1356
01:09:21,722 --> 01:09:24,595
and he knows
that he can pull a rabbit

1357
01:09:24,638 --> 01:09:25,987
out of a hat if he needs to,

1358
01:09:26,031 --> 01:09:28,990
and I've seen him do it.

1359
01:09:29,034 --> 01:09:31,254
He'll enter into a project

1360
01:09:31,297 --> 01:09:35,214
because of very strong beliefs
about it,

1361
01:09:35,258 --> 01:09:37,434
even if they are
conflicted beliefs

1362
01:09:37,477 --> 01:09:41,264
or if there's no way
to know the actual truth

1363
01:09:41,307 --> 01:09:44,136
or the actual outcome
of what's gonna happen.

1364
01:09:44,180 --> 01:09:46,138
You know, as long
as you're excited

1365
01:09:46,182 --> 01:09:51,056
and fascinated and curious,
you're alive.

1366
01:09:51,099 --> 01:09:52,318
You're really living.

1367
01:09:52,362 --> 01:09:54,277
And he's really living.

1368
01:09:54,320 --> 01:09:56,670
He's often described it
as being a surfer.

1369
01:09:56,714 --> 01:09:58,629
You know, you have no idea
if you're gonna catch the wave.

1370
01:09:58,672 --> 01:10:00,370
You have no idea,
once you're on the wave,

1371
01:10:00,413 --> 01:10:02,067
how long you're gonna stay
on the wave,

1372
01:10:02,110 --> 01:10:04,852
and you don't know
when your ride is over.

1373
01:10:04,896 --> 01:10:08,291
And for him,
that's hugely exciting.

1374
01:10:08,334 --> 01:10:12,556
- Have you ever pulled
something that's failed?

1375
01:10:12,599 --> 01:10:13,557
- No.

1376
01:10:13,600 --> 01:10:15,515
- No, really?

1377
01:10:15,559 --> 01:10:17,038
Is it that easy?

1378
01:10:17,082 --> 01:10:18,910
Is there a--
I mean, is there any kind

1379
01:10:18,953 --> 01:10:20,955
of surefire thing you can do?

1380
01:10:20,999 --> 01:10:23,480
- It's like producing
a theater piece.

1381
01:10:23,523 --> 01:10:25,873
You conceive, write, produce,
direct, stage, act in it.

1382
01:10:25,917 --> 01:10:27,875
It's very complicated.

1383
01:10:27,919 --> 01:10:30,313
There are many techniques
to gaining access to the media.

1384
01:10:30,356 --> 01:10:32,184
If you know how the media works,

1385
01:10:32,228 --> 01:10:35,274
it's kind of easy
to give them the hook.

1386
01:10:35,318 --> 01:10:38,495
- I know that he will
never stop being creative,

1387
01:10:38,538 --> 01:10:40,497
doing projects,

1388
01:10:40,540 --> 01:10:45,502
coming up with outrageous,
outlandish, hilarious ideas.

1389
01:10:45,545 --> 01:10:46,590
I know he won't.

1390
01:10:46,633 --> 01:10:49,201
It's just his nature.

1391
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:50,942
It's what he'll do.

1392
01:10:50,985 --> 01:10:53,684
- You never know what he's
gonna come up with next.

1393
01:10:53,727 --> 01:10:55,903
You never know
where he's going,

1394
01:10:55,947 --> 01:10:57,470
but I'm going with him.

1395
01:10:57,514 --> 01:10:59,733
I'm gonna be there
every time he calls,

1396
01:10:59,777 --> 01:11:01,518
even at this age.

1397
01:11:01,561 --> 01:11:03,911
I'm gonna follow him
through the streets of New York.

1398
01:11:03,955 --> 01:11:07,306
It's okay because
I know, wherever he's going,

1399
01:11:07,350 --> 01:11:09,526
it's gonna be fun.

1400
01:11:11,484 --> 01:11:13,704
- And, you know, we were leaving
one of the houses recently,

1401
01:11:13,747 --> 01:11:14,966
and he said, "I'm so lucky.

1402
01:11:15,009 --> 01:11:16,837
"I'm so, so lucky

1403
01:11:16,881 --> 01:11:19,840
"that all of my friends
are here doing this for me.

1404
01:11:19,884 --> 01:11:23,017
Like, it doesn't escape me for
a second how grateful I am."

1405
01:11:23,061 --> 01:11:26,020
And then he looked at me in
the rearview mirror and said,

1406
01:11:26,064 --> 01:11:28,501
"And you're one
of my new friends."

1407
01:11:31,896 --> 01:11:33,593
- I've been really lucky
that I've been able

1408
01:11:33,637 --> 01:11:36,422
to live the life
that I have lived

1409
01:11:36,466 --> 01:11:39,860
and with the people
that have come into my life,

1410
01:11:39,904 --> 01:11:41,949
and to feel a part,

1411
01:11:41,993 --> 01:11:44,387
that we've all
created something,

1412
01:11:44,430 --> 01:11:47,607
because, you know,
it's just not all me.

1413
01:11:47,651 --> 01:11:51,959
It's me involving
everyone I can involve,

1414
01:11:52,003 --> 01:11:54,135
and everyone doing it.

1415
01:11:54,179 --> 01:11:55,615
And that, I love.

1416
01:11:55,659 --> 01:11:59,184
That's the we.
It's not the me.

